Insurers paid out more than £1 billion to flooded-out householders last year, making it the most expensive year for claims in five years.
According to official figures from the Association of British Insurers, some 486,000 homeowners made claims for flood and storm damage last year, equivalent to 1,330 a day.
With the average payout hitting £18,200, the final bill for insurers reached £1.19 billion, the ABI said.
